Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.52,0:00:26.33,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是个真实的故事...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.92,0:00:35.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,英国  泽西岛  1879
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.54,0:01:48.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你们是谁  \NWho are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.78,0:01:50.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你们在做什么  \NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.78,0:01:53.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们将把这建成高尔夫球场\NThere's a golf Iinks going in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.66,0:01:55.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,高尔夫球是什么东西  \NWhat's golf?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.66,0:01:59.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,高尔夫球是绅士们玩的比赛\NGolf is a game played by gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:01.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是你这样的人玩的\NNot for the Iikes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.46,0:02:04.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快走开  孩子\NNow, run along, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.51,0:04:50.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,布鲁克莱恩  马萨诸塞州  1900
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:11.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在这儿  先生\NHere it is, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.14,0:06:05.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快点  我们走\NCome on! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.42,0:06:51.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就是这样  坐直  莎拉\NThat's it. Sit up straight, Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:55.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,轻轻拉缰绳\NLightly on the reins. There.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.98,0:07:04.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是我们要做的  弗朗西斯\NThis is how we do it, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.66,0:07:08.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们努力工作  把钱拿回家\NWe work hard, and we bring home the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:17.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,努力工作  把钱拿回家\NWork hard. Bring home the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.62,0:07:52.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-吉尔勒莫  -是\N- Guillermo! - Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.02,0:07:54.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快点\NCome on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.10,0:08:45.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  你究竟在做什么  \NFrancis, what in the world are you doin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.26,0:08:48.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,已经后半夜了\NIt's after midnight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:52.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你会吵醒你弟弟的  上床去\NYou're keepin' your brother up. Go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:57.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,雷德蒙  上床睡觉  不许说话\NRaymond, go to sleep. No talkin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.02,0:09:00.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我的意思是  不要发出声音\NNo noises. I mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.42,0:09:08.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你在干吗  弗朗西斯  \NWhat have you got there, Francis? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.66,0:09:11.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯\NFrancis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.90,0:09:16.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我能去看他吗  爸爸\NCan I see him, Father? PIease?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:18.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他在说什么  看谁  \NWhat's he talking about? See who?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.90,0:09:20.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利·瓦顿\NHarry Vardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:28.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,打这种比赛的绅士\NAny gentleman who plays this game
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:31.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,没有一个是你的朋友\Nis not a friend to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.10,0:09:32.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.74,0:09:34.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但他是目前最出色的\NBut he's the greatest ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.62,0:09:38.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-亚瑟  我想这没有什么坏处  -不要说了\N- Arthur, I don't see the harm in... - Not another word.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.06,0:09:42.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他今天得去学校\NThe boy goes to school today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.46,0:09:44.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就谈到这儿\NThat's the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.14,0:09:53.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,达西小姐  帮我照顾下小孩\NMrs. Darcy, mind the Iittle one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.50,0:09:55.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他会去爬楼梯的\NHe'II try to climb those stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.42,0:09:58.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  放下书\NFrancis, Ieave your books.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.94,0:10:02.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我要去买东西  你跟我一起去\NI've got shoppin' to do. You come with me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.34,0:10:04.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,爸爸说我得去学校\NFather said I had to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.42,0:10:06.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你一天不去学校没有关系\NYou can miss school for one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:09.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,而且我需要人帮提包  走吧\NBesides, I need help with me packages. Come along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.74,0:10:32.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是什么事情引起这么大的骚动  \NWhat could be causing such a fuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:37.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,去吧  我会去找你\NGo on. I'II find ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.90,0:11:18.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢  女士们  先生们\NThank you, Iadies and gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:20.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我希望你们能帮忙\NI'II now presume upon your goodwill
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.06,0:11:23.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我需要个志愿者\Nand request the services of a volunteer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:26.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谁愿意上来  \NAnyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.46,0:11:36.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你好  你叫什么名字  \NHello. What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.98,0:11:39.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-弗朗西斯  -你好  弗朗西斯先生\N- Francis. - Hello, Mr. Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:44.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道这是什么吗  \NNow, do you know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.78,0:11:47.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,高尔夫球杆\NA brassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:49.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  打一杆吧\NSo it is. Have a bash.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.10,0:12:05.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,继续\NGo on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:12.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不错  弗朗西斯  即使在最灰暗的日子\NThat's all right, Francis. Even in our darkest hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.14,0:12:15.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们也得时刻记住  我们永不绝望\Nwe must always remember, you never despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.18,0:12:17.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你有没有把一只小鸟握在手上过  \NHave you held a Iive bird in your hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.58,0:12:20.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,握的时候不能太用力  否则会伤到它\NNot too hard to hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.82,0:12:23.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只要不让它飞走就可以了\NJust firm enough to stop it from flying away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.02,0:12:27.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,再试试\NTry it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.66,0:12:40.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到了吗  \NDid you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.50,0:13:10.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,欢迎常胜将军\NHail the conquering hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.94,0:13:12.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,达尔文先生\NMr. Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.30,0:13:16.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-是不是如同我所想的一样  -我不确定  哈利\N- Is this what I think it is? - I'm not sure, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.06,0:13:19.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我跟你一样\NI received a summons from Lord Northcliffe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.42,0:13:21.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-得到了诺斯克利夫爵士的召唤  -不用找了\N- just as you did. - Keep the change, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.70,0:13:24.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-他正在里面等着  -今天是特别的一天\N- He's waiting inside. - Today's the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.66,0:13:27.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是  哈利  从没有一个非职业选手\NBut, Harry, no professional has ever been asked
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:30.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,加入过绅士们的高尔夫俱乐部\Nto join a gentlemen's golf club as a member.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.10,0:13:32.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,任何事都会有个开始  伯纳德\NFirst time for everything, Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.18,0:13:33.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-是的  -瞧瞧这个地方\N- Yes. - Look at this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.90,0:13:35.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们为什么会让你过来  \NWhy else would they want you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.98,0:13:38.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他不信任我  我只是为他工作\NHe doesn't confide in me. I only work for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.06,0:13:44.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,十年前  我还是个修剪篱笆的\NTen years ago, I was clippin' hedges.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.94,0:13:53.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不可思议\NMarvelous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.38,0:13:57.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,干得太漂亮了  哈利\NBrilliantly done, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.42,0:14:00.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢你  先生\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.62,0:14:04.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你们这些绅士愿意  把它加入到你们的战利品\NI'd be honored if you gentlemen would consider
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.22,0:14:07.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我将感到很荣幸  -一个闪闪发光的奖杯\N- adding it to your trophy case. - A glittering addition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:10.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们很高兴为你保留这个  是吧  奈维尔  \NWe'd be pleased to keep it for you. Wouldn't we, Neville?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.54,0:14:12.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你很大方\NHandsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:15.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不过你要想再拿回去  恐怕就不是那么容易了\NBut you might not get it back without a tussle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.02,0:14:18.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我也没想过能轻松的把它拿回来\NDon't plan on handing it back myself without a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.78,0:14:21.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利  进入正题吧\NHarry, I'II come to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:23.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们俱乐部有个公开赛\NWe've had an opening at our club.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.34,0:14:27.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这位是布洛克爵士  俱乐部委员会主席\NLord Bullock chairs the membership committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.10,0:14:29.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你父亲是做什么的  \NWhat does your father do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.58,0:14:31.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,先生  他是泽西岛上的一个园丁\NUh, he's a gardener on Jersey, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.90,0:14:33.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我听说你是信奉罗马天主教的\NI'm told you're Church of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.58,0:14:36.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你母亲是法国人吗  -是的\N- Mother's French? - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:40.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想我们可以暂时不管这个\NI believe we can work around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:44.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就这么决定了  你是我们想找的人\NIt's decided, then. You're just the man for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.90,0:14:55.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嗯  我都不知道说什么了  先生\NWell, I don't know what to say, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.50,0:14:57.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  就说好吧\NWell, say yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.54,0:14:59.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们希望你替我们工作  有相当好的收入\NWe want you to work for us. Decent wage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.94,0:15:01.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以经营自己的店\NYou can run your own shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.70,0:15:04.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,当然还可以开班上课  收取你想要的费用\NLessons, of course. Charge what you Iike for those.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.98,0:15:07.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你是唯一一个能帮我解决问题的人\NYou're the only man who can set me right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.70,0:15:10.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你得停止你的工作\NYou'II have your work cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.10,0:15:12.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想到处都是酒\NI think it's drinks all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:14.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我说过  你替我们工作  \NI'm told you'll work for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.90,0:15:16.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,高尔夫球是绅士们打的比赛\NGolf is a game played by gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.98,0:15:19.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是你这样的人玩的  绅士们打的比赛\NNot for the likes of you. Played by gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.46,0:15:21.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,可以经营你自己的商店  有相当好的收入\NRun your own shop. Decent wage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:23.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快走开  小孩\NRun along, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:48.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  已经下半夜了\NFrancis. It's after midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.30,0:15:49.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,妈妈  最后一个球\NJust one more, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.82,0:16:20.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,黑斯廷斯先生  \NMr. Hastings!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.26,0:16:23.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-啊  弗朗西斯大师  -先生\N- Ah, Master Francis. - Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:25.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们现在需要一个实战\NWe now Iack but one essential
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.74,0:16:28.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,来完成我们的既定目标\Nto complete the swift appointment of our round:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:31.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你的俱乐部赛  -我的俱乐部赛吗  先生  \N- Your clubs. - My clubs, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.22,0:16:35.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,球童是不能打全程的  如果坎贝尔先生发现我在  \NCaddies aren't allowed on the course. If Mr. Campbell sees me out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:39.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我来帮你考虑坎贝尔的事  你快去  挥动那些球棒\NYou Iet me worry about Campbell. Go. Get those clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.14,0:16:41.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快去  孩子  挥动那些球棒\NYou go, boy. Get those clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.26,0:17:02.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-挥杆不错  伙计  -谢谢  先生\N- Well struck, Iad. - Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.70,0:17:59.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你用了多少杆  \NWhat did you shoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:01.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,81杆  先生\NUh, an 81, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.30,0:18:03.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,第15洞你用了多少杆  \NWhat did you take on 1 5?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.46,0:18:04.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,9杆  先生\NA nine, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.90,0:18:06.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,第一次在新英格兰最难的场地\NSo you shot an 81 first time around
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.98,0:18:09.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,打完全程用了81杆  \Non the toughest golf course in New England?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.94,0:18:12.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-其中有个洞还用了9杆  -嗯  我  我想我  \N- With a nine? - Well, I... I think I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:16.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我看到你站在那儿  知道球童是不允许打  \NI saw you standing there, knowing caddies aren't supposed to play...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.70,0:18:18.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,继续说\NGo on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.62,0:18:21.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我  我想我有些紧张  先生\NI... I think I got a Iittle nervous, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.06,0:18:24.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们得看看你是如何控制自己的\NWe needed to see how you handled yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:26.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,控制我自己  \NHandled myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:30.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,下个月有全国业余锦标赛\NNational Amateur Championship's here next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.66,0:18:35.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你是说  我可以  \NAre you saying that I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.82,0:18:37.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我该做什么  \NWhat do I have to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.86,0:18:40.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你得去跟那些有资格的人比赛  -很容易的\N- You have to play in the qualifier. - That's the easy part.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.90,0:18:43.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你要让竞赛委员同意你参赛\NYou have to be approved by the executive committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:46.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你是这儿的球童吗  \NYou're a caddie here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.42,0:18:48.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  做了10年\NYes, sir. For ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.62,0:18:51.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,为了成为业余选手  最近已经不作了\NI recently resigned to preserve my status as an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.62,0:18:54.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,什么  没有计划做职业选手吗  \NWhat, no plans to turn professional?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.38,0:18:57.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,没有  我准备从商\NUh, no, sir. I plan to have a career in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:18:59.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-哦  做生意  -是的\N- Oh, business? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.78,0:19:01.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,什么样的生意  \NWhat sort of business?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.42,0:19:03.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,霍华德  我们得  \NHoward, we need...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:05.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  你们继续吧\NSorry. Carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.22,0:19:07.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你的主俱乐部在哪儿  这上面没写\NWhat's your home club? I don't see it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.90,0:19:09.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们得赞助你\NThey have to sponsor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我的主俱乐部  \NMy home club?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.86,0:19:17.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我正在多个俱乐部之间选择  -哦  听好了\N- I'm between clubs at the moment. - Look, see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.50,0:19:19.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你可能有资格做一个选手\Nyou may have qualified as a player,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.50,0:19:22.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但这不是球童做的事情\Nbut this just isn't the sort of thing that caddies do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.54,0:19:25.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你是个球童  \NYou're a caddie?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:26.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  先生  我曾经是\NYes, sir, I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.74,0:19:30.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,球童不能进行业余选手比赛  你不能参加这比赛\NCaddies don't play in the Amateur. It's not for your kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.18,0:19:32.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只有会员才可以参加\NMembers only.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.10,0:19:34.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们场地委员会要讨论公开赛的问题了\NWe need to discuss the opening on the greens committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:36.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  但是  总可以让那些\NI'm sorry. But there must be a way
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:39.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,非会员的人也来参加比赛吧\Nfor somebody who's not a member to compete.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.54,0:19:41.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,今年不行\NNot this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.06,0:19:49.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他能支付50美元的入场费\NAs if he could afford the $50 entrance fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:54.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  先生\NExcuse me. Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.30,0:19:56.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我能支付50美元的话  \N...if I were to pay the $50,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.08,0:19:57.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是不是我就可以加入俱乐部了\Nwould I need to belong to a club?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.78,0:19:58.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,理论上不可以\NTechnically, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.50,0:20:06.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你仍然需要一个有名望的俱乐部成员  来担保  而且  \NYou would still need a club member in good standing to sponsor you, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.78,0:20:09.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,而且  由我来担保\NAnd... that would be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.62,0:20:13.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,打高尔夫球要50美元\NFifty dollars to play golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:16.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我会把挣的钱全部拿回家的\NI'II pay back every penny from my earnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.30,0:20:19.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我对你很失望  弗朗西斯  这就是你从我这儿学到的吗  \NIs this how I failed you? Is that all you've Iearned from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.66,0:20:21.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是的  先生  但这只是场比赛\NNo, sir. But it's just a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:23.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,比赛  \NA game?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.90,0:20:27.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,比赛不能让一个男人过活  不能让他养家\NA game doesn't give a man what he needs to make a Iife, feed his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.94,0:20:29.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你说的对  但是如果我赢了  就会有伟大的事情发生\NIf I win, great things could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.94,0:20:31.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,什么也不会发生\NNothing will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.74,0:20:35.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们会按他们的喜好来利用你\NThey'II use you for their own amusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.42,0:20:38.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我能成功的  这是我所擅长的\NI can do this. This is something I'm good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.62,0:20:41.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果是你  你会怎么做  \NWhat if you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.54,0:20:43.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么来获得那50美元  \NWhat will you get for your $50?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:49.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我也有过梦想  弗朗西斯\NI had dreams too, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.66,0:20:52.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,无论你做什么\NNo matter what you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:54.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们都不会让你通过那条街的\Nthey'II never Iet you cross that street.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.62,0:20:58.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想要的就是个机会\NAII I want is a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.54,0:21:06.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好的\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.42,0:21:10.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们打个赌吧\NOK, we make a bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.78,0:21:14.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你发誓  如果你输了  就不再打高尔夫球\NYou promise me if you Iose, no more golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.30,0:21:15.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你得放弃那愚蠢的比赛\NYou give up this fool's game.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.98,0:21:18.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,去完成你的学业  你得学贸易\NYou finish your schooling, you Iearn a trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.78,0:21:22.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,把你靠诚实劳动获得的钱拿回家\Nand you bring home an honest wage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.66,0:21:25.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是说我不合格吗  \NIf I don't qualify?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.46,0:21:28.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好的  我答应你\NYes, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.82,0:22:00.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是英文版的  这儿都没有出版\NIt's the English edition. It's not even in print here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.14,0:22:03.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利·瓦顿\NHarry Vardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.50,0:22:07.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:10.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好好学习吧\NRead it, study it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:13.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须打到78杆  才有资格\NYou'II need a 78 to qualify.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.50,0:22:15.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,艰苦的竞赛\NStiffer competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.30,0:22:17.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们是这个国家最好的业余选手\NThese are the best amateurs in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.30,0:22:20.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你认为我能行吗  \NDo you think I'm ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.78,0:22:23.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我不知道  只有你参加了后  你才能知道\NI don't know, and neither will you until you're in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.62,0:22:26.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只是高尔夫球比赛  是冠军杯\NThere's golf, and there's championship golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.70,0:22:34.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,帮我保管一下  我要去参加舞会\NKeep it for me. I'm going to the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.50,0:22:39.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们说邀请所有的选手参加\NThey said all the players are invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.18,0:22:43.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,舞会是什么样的  \NWhat's it Iike in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.54,0:22:46.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我也不知道  我不能进去\NI couldn't tell you. I'm not allowed inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.86,0:23:36.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,能帮我一下吗  \NDo me a favor, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.42,0:23:42.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  这个男孩我以前见过  在去学校的时候他在后面追我\NHi. This boy I used to see before I Ieft for college is after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.98,0:23:45.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-假装你要请我跳舞  -你在这啊  小甜心\N- Pretend you asked me to dance. - There you are, you peach.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.06,0:23:48.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你不能整晚都躲我\NYou know, you can't avoid me all evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.34,0:23:51.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我说过要跳一支舞  菲利普\NI... I said a dance, Phillip.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.94,0:23:53.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但不是这支\NNot this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.54,0:23:56.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我答应这位  -弗朗西斯·奥密特\N- I promised this one to... - Francis Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.18,0:23:59.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我知道你家族吗  -不清楚\N- Do I know your family? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.38,0:24:01.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-菲利普·韦恩赖特  -韦恩赖特  \N- Phillip Wainwright? - Wainwright?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.30,0:24:03.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,啊  是的  韦恩赖特家族  很好的人\NOh, yes. Wainwrights, good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.34,0:24:04.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,韦恩赖特家族\NWainwrights.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.26,0:24:12.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好了  时间还早  她会和你跳舞的\NWell, the evening's young. She'II catch up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.02,0:24:19.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你真是个好伙伴  帮了我大忙\NYou're a real sport for helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.02,0:24:21.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,又没有什么麻烦\NIt's no trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.30,0:24:27.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我今天疯了\NI had the craziest day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.98,0:24:32.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我从费城坐火车来  我把包丢在巴尔的摩了\NI take a train from Philadelphia, my bags end up in Baltimore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.22,0:24:34.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我的晚礼服也给落在巴尔的摩了\NMy tux is in the bags in Baltimore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.22,0:24:38.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我现在穿的是男仆的衣服\NI'm wearing the houseman's suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.70,0:24:43.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不过你看起来不错\NI think you Iook just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.86,0:24:45.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你也是\NYou too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.98,0:24:49.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他走了吗  \NIs he gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.50,0:24:53.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,没有  他还在看着\NNo, he's still watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.18,0:24:54.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们跳支舞  好吗  \NShall we dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.14,0:25:12.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你刚才说你要去上大学  是吗  \NYou said you were going to college?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.82,0:25:14.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,史密斯学院  第一个学期\NSmith. First semester.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.02,0:25:16.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.46,0:25:18.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你呢  \NWhere are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.94,0:25:20.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,读哪所大学  \NTo college?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.90,0:25:26.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我要花一年时间考虑一下我的选择\NI'm taking the year off to consider my options.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.90,0:25:29.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想这是明智之举\NI think that's so wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.50,0:25:31.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,可能你会去欧洲\NPerhaps you'II go to Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.22,0:25:34.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,可能吧  因为我的家在法国\NPerhaps I will. 'Cause I have family in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.78,0:25:39.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  你能不能再说一次你的名字  \NI'm sorry. What did you say your name was again?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.62,0:25:42.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯·奥密特\NFrancis. Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.90,0:25:46.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  瞧  那是我哥哥\NOh, Iook! There's my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.70,0:25:54.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-弗雷迪  来认识一下弗朗西斯  -弗雷迪\N- Freddie, you must know Francis. - Freddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.18,0:25:58.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,球童\NCaddie Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.42,0:26:00.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗雷迪  你真会开玩笑\NFreddie, you're such a kidder.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.50,0:26:05.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,爸妈  这是弗朗西斯·奥密特\NDad, Mother, this is Francis Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.22,0:26:06.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你好\NHow do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.94,0:26:08.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,衣服很漂亮\NThat's a beautiful dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.94,0:26:10.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯是个比赛选手\NFrancis is playing in the tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.06,0:26:12.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  我知道\NYes, yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.90,0:26:17.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你们男人谈吧  我和妈妈一会过来\NWell, you boys chat. Mother and I will be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.26,0:26:27.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你女儿很漂亮\NSwell girl, your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.86,0:26:31.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,年轻人  你可以被邀请过来\NYoung man, you may have been invited,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.02,0:26:34.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是你别指望你能属于这\Nbut don't get the idea that you belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.82,0:26:56.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,有两类选手\NThere are only two types of player:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.10,0:26:59.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一类是绷着神经要赢比赛\NThose who keep their nerves in control and win championships,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.34,0:27:01.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,另一类却相反\Nand those who do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.94,0:28:36.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,最多只能用5杆  你就能进入下一轮了\NFive or Iess, and you make the cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.02,0:28:40.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,第18洞  我闭着眼睛都只用5杆\NEighteen? I can make five here in my sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.50,0:28:51.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,搞定\NThat's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.14,0:29:55.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,祝贺你\NCongratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.82,0:29:57.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,太糟糕了  球童\NThat's too bad, Caddie Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.54,0:29:59.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以在比赛中当我的球童\NYou could caddie for me in the tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.74,0:30:02.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你还是有用的  不是吗  \NYou're available, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.38,0:30:05.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,祝贺你  儿子  打得不错\NCongratulations, son. Well played.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.98,0:31:45.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,要组建帝国  哈利\NEmpire, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.66,0:31:49.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,否则阳光永远不会照到我们  一群废物\NThe sun never sets on us, all that rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.66,0:31:53.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,说到荣耀  希腊的亚历山大是最伟大的\NConsider the glory that was Greece of AIexander the Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.94,0:31:56.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,现在你在地图上都找不到\NNow you can't even find it on a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.66,0:32:01.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,希腊将体育运动传播给世界\NGreece introduced sport to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.10,0:32:03.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,纯粹地表达他们的优越感\Npure expression of their superiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.54,0:32:05.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们应该走他们的路\NWe've trodden that same road.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.94,0:32:09.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,足球  板球  橄榄球  高尔夫球\NFootball, cricket, rugby, golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.50,0:32:12.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让英国能举办所有重要的锦标赛\NAII the major championships remain in British hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.02,0:32:14.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,得一分\NSave one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.86,0:32:18.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你有什么打算  \NWhat are you proposing?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.22,0:32:20.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,美国公开赛\NThe U.S. Open.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.02,0:32:24.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你以前赢过的\NYou won it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.18,0:32:26.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我要你对美国人展开\NI want you to mount a new campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.62,0:32:28.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一场新的战役\Nto do to the Americans
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.58,0:32:31.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就像亚历山大对波斯人做的那样\Nwhat AIexander did to the Persians.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.42,0:32:34.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让他们都变成废物\NLay waste to 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.06,0:32:38.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我的书会占领所有市场\NMy papers get exclusive coverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.30,0:32:41.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,伯纳德会在一旁把你的胜利记录在册\NBernard here comes along to chronicle your conquest.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.78,0:32:43.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我们的比赛\NIt's our game, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.58,0:32:47.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,从他们的公开赛上  把奖杯拿回来\NWin their Open and bring back that trophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.94,0:32:51.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,当然  奖金归你\NYou pocket your winnings, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.78,0:32:56.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-不用出路费吗  先生  -所有的费用都不用\N- Wouldn't pay for the crossing, sir. - AII expenses paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.26,0:32:59.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,正好搞个展览巡游  主办方安排一切\NAs part of an exhibition tour, all sponsors arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.62,0:33:01.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,有兴趣吗  \NDoes that cover it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.94,0:33:06.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好的  那就做吧\NYep. That'd do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.86,0:33:08.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我还听到一些关于\NAnd I hear there's talk
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.50,0:33:10.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,俱乐部成员荣誉的谈论\Nof an honorary membership at the club.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.02,0:33:12.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也能够一起解决\NThis would clinch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.90,0:33:16.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我料想国王会对英格兰  最伟大的运动员\NAnd I daresay His Majesty might want to show his gratitude
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.14,0:33:18.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,表示谢意的\Nto England's greatest sportsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.26,0:33:21.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利·瓦顿  大英帝国\NHarry Vardon, Order of the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.30,0:33:23.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,会给你带上一枚漂亮的戒指\NHas a nice ring to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.78,0:33:30.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我需要一个合作伙伴  能和我分享的伙伴\NI'II need a partner. Somebody to share the workload with.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.90,0:33:32.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这正是我所想的\NMy thoughts exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.90,0:33:35.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,威尔弗雷德跟你去  他是大不列颠业余比赛冠军\NWilfred here is your man. Top amateur in the British Isles.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.98,0:33:37.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,太荣幸了\NDelighted, old chap.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.66,0:33:39.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,高兴得合不拢嘴了  是吧  \NJolly good wheeze, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.78,0:33:42.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,给那些美国佬一个沉重的打击\NGiving the Yanks a thorough thrashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.66,0:33:49.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我有人选了\NI had someone else in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.14,0:33:54.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,特德·雷  \NTed Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.58,0:33:55.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪  他是西哥特人\NChrist, he's a Visigoth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.06,0:33:57.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不  他是泽西人\NNo, he's a Jerseyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.74,0:34:00.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,借过\N'Scuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.74,0:34:14.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,下注结束  \NAII bets off!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.94,0:34:25.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-快点  -快点\N- Come on! - Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.62,0:34:41.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-特德  -哈利\N- Ted! - Harry!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.66,0:34:44.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  瞧瞧\NHey! Look at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.86,0:34:48.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是你手下的大师  \NWhat's this, another night out with your ruling class masters?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.38,0:34:51.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是特德·雷  这位是诺斯克利夫爵士\NTed Ray, Lord Northcliffe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.10,0:34:54.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,诺斯克利夫爵士  非常荣幸\NLord Northcliffe? The honor is entirely mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.94,0:35:01.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么过来了  哈利\NWhat brings you down this way, Harry?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.38,0:35:09.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你好  你好\NHello, hello
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.86,0:35:11.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,停止你的游戏吧\NStop your little games
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.86,0:35:15.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不要以为这就是适合你的路  \NDon't you think your ways you ought to mend
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.10,0:35:32.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你相信吗  他们把公开赛推迟了三个月\NCan you believe they moved the Open back three months
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.90,0:35:34.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就是为了让一个家伙参赛  \Njust so one guy can play in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.82,0:35:36.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,啊  他可是哈利·瓦顿\NWell, he's Harry Vardon,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.38,0:35:38.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,设计师  灰狗[哈利·瓦顿的绰号]\NThe Stylist, The Greyhound.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.62,0:35:40.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他住在月球上  我就不关心\NI don't care if he's the man in the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.78,0:35:42.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们不可能为一个美国人这么做的\NThey wouldn't do that for an American.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.02,0:35:45.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,问问弗朗西斯  他以前参加过\NAsk Francis. He used to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.38,0:35:49.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你参加过  -不  没有\N- You did? - No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.86,0:35:51.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈  他这是谦虚\NAh, he's being modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.78,0:35:53.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他过去很优秀的  不过他放弃了\NHe used to be good before he gave it up
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.98,0:35:56.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,为了做生意  是这样的吗  弗朗西斯  \Nfor the glamour of retail. Isn't that right, Francis?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.06,0:36:00.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  \NFrancis!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.54,0:36:02.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  \NFrancis!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.14,0:36:09.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,凯西要与金发碧眼的姑娘跳华尔兹\NCasey would waltz with the strawberry blonde
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.90,0:36:14.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,乐队一直在演奏\NAnd the band played on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.22,0:36:18.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他与心爱的姑娘在地上轻轻的移动\NHe'd glide 'cross the floor with the girl he adored
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.62,0:36:22.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,乐队一直在演奏\NAnd the band played on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.66,0:36:27.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他的脑袋紧张欲裂\NHis brain was so loaded it nearly exploded
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.34,0:36:31.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,可怜的姑娘被惊慌摇晃\NThe poor girl would shake with alarm
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.22,0:36:33.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他永远不会离开\NHe 'd ne 'er leave the girl
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.74,0:36:37.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这个有草莓卷一样秀发的姑娘\NWith the strawberry curl
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.94,0:36:43.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,乐队一直在演奏\NAnd the band played on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.10,0:37:08.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,意大利语演唱
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.50,0:38:17.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  太动听了\NOh, well. It was glorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.86,0:38:21.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-是不是很动听  -是的\N- Wasn't it glorious? - Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.18,0:38:22.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你以前听过这样的声音吗  \NHave you ever heard such a voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:29.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就像  音乐就像从某个地方发出来\NIt was Iike the... the music was coming through her
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.26,0:38:31.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,穿透她的身体一样\Nfrom someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.54,0:38:35.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是我的感受  我常常想  \NThat's the feeling I've always wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.86,0:38:41.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  想什么  \NFrancis, for what? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.30,0:38:59.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他在那儿  弗朗西斯  过来一下\NThere he is. Francis! Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.34,0:39:00.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,过来见一下罗伯特·沃森\NMeet Robert Watson,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.70,0:39:03.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,美国高尔夫球协会会长\Npresident of the United States Golf Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.22,0:39:07.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  很高兴见到你\NFrancis, pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.10,0:39:08.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,很高兴见到您\NWell, the pleasure's mine, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.06,0:39:11.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嗯  我找个售货员  来给你介绍一下我们的产品\NUh, Iet me have a salesman show you our equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.66,0:39:14.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-这是波士顿最好的商店  -他不是来买球棍的\N- It's the best selection in Boston. - He's not here to buy clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.94,0:39:17.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我听说你住在布鲁克林  离国家俱乐部不远\NI hear you Iive in Brookline, not far from the country club.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.02,0:39:19.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就在街对面\NRight across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.42,0:39:22.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们将在那儿举行公开赛  为期2个星期\NWe're holding our Open Championship there in two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.98,0:39:25.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你被提名了  -提名  先生  \N- Your name came up. - My name, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.06,0:39:28.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们准备让当地的一名业余选手参加\NI'm Iooking to add a Iocal amateur to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.54,0:39:31.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利·瓦顿也来参赛了  还有特德·雷\NHarry Vardon's playing. And Ted Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.46,0:39:40.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,沃森先生  很感谢  但是我不能接受\NMr. Watson, thank you, but I can't accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.86,0:39:43.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-为什么不  -这儿的工作很忙\N- Why not? - I'm awfully busy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.46,0:39:46.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嗯  我不再打高尔夫了\NAnd, uh, I don't play golf anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.30,0:39:51.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你多大了  弗朗西斯  -20了  先生\N- How old are you, Francis? - I'm 20, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.14,0:39:55.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这个年龄放弃梦想  太年轻了  不是吗  \NAwfully young to be giving up on your dreams, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.10,0:39:57.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我只是有特殊的原因  就是这样\NI just have different ones now, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.42,0:40:01.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  黑斯廷斯先生\NI'm sorry, Mr. Hastings.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.10,0:40:03.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,没有必要解释  弗朗西斯\NThere's no need to explain, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.90,0:40:06.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,祝你好运\NAII the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.42,0:41:09.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这个挥杆好熟悉啊\NThat swing Iooks familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.82,0:41:12.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你来这儿做什么  \NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.50,0:41:14.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我父亲带我出来走走\NFather's taking me out for our annual round.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.50,0:41:17.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我哥哥说你在这儿工作\NMy brother said that you were working here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.78,0:41:20.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你哥哥  我在这儿见过他几次\NYour brother. I've seen him in here a couple times.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.06,0:41:24.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我希望你能卖给我些装备\NI was hoping you could sell me some equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.46,0:41:27.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我实际上不是个销售人员\NI'm not actually the salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.26,0:41:30.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,还在思考你的选择吗  \NStill considering your options?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.34,0:41:31.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.46,0:41:38.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我去帮你找个销售员来\NI'II go get you a salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.90,0:42:04.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好的\NAII right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.62,0:42:13.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利·瓦顿\NHarry Vardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.30,0:42:16.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,设计师[哈利·瓦顿的绰号]正在进行练习赛\NThe Stylist. Practice round.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.78,0:42:26.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们期待有大量的观众  所以邀请名人很重要\NWe're expecting a big turnout, so it's important we have marshals here...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.70,0:42:28.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,沃森先生  弗朗西斯·奥密特\NMr. Watson. Francis Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.22,0:42:30.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我能和你谈一下吗  先生  -什么事  \N- Can I speak to you, sir? - What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.86,0:42:33.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果出价合适的话  我愿意为你参加比赛\NIf that offer is still good, I'd Iove to take you up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.66,0:42:35.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,现在很忙  我们得考虑一下\NWe have to think about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.30,0:42:38.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我不要钱  -你能给我们些时间吗  弗朗西斯  \N- I'm not asking for favors... - Can you give us a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.42,0:42:40.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,格罗夫大街怎么样  \NWhat about Grove Street?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.38,0:42:55.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天一大早来这儿见我\NMeet me here, sunup.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.54,0:42:58.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你有些工作要做\NYou've got some work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.60,0:43:55.61,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,1913  美国公开赛资格赛
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.78,0:43:58.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,比利  我们在哪儿  \NBilly, where do we stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.38,0:44:00.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,抽到76号签\NCut Iine's 76.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.18,0:44:02.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,用4杆完成6号洞\NSix holes to make up four shots.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.58,0:44:36.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么啦  有什么问题吗  \NWhat is it? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.82,0:44:39.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你刚才在6号洞打出了小鸟球  -真的吗  \N- You just made six straight birdies. - I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.82,0:44:42.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,祝贺你  小伙子  你进入公开赛了\NCongratulations, Iad. You're in the Open.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.78,0:44:52.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,先生们\NGentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.38,0:44:57.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不管是职业选手  还是业余选手\NI want to welcome you all, professionals and amateurs alike,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.46,0:45:00.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,欢迎来参加第八届美国公开赛\Nto the 1 8th United States Open Championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.34,0:45:09.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在接下来的两天  有4轮高尔夫球赛\NFour rounds of golf to be played over the next two days
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.34,0:45:11.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,通过比赛选出世界上最好的选手\Nto identify the best player in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.94,0:45:13.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让我们欢迎\NLet's give a special welcome
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.02,0:45:17.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,大不列颠业余比赛冠军  威尔弗雷德·里德\Nto the British Amateur Champion, Mr. Wilfred Reid...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.42,0:45:21.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,还有著名的职业选手\N...and our famous professional visitors,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.90,0:45:23.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哈利·瓦顿和特德·雷\NHarry Vardon and Ted Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.94,0:45:31.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们防守方的冠军\NI'II yield the floor to our defending champion,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.82,0:45:34.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,欢迎来自费城的职业选手约翰·麦克德莫特\Na professional from Philadelphia, John McDermott.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.10,0:45:47.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你看报纸的话  上面有很多消息\NIf you read the papers, there's a Iot of talk
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.62,0:45:51.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,关于伟大英国冠军远渡来到这  参加我们的公开赛的消息\Nabout the great English champions sailing over here to play in our Open.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.90,0:45:54.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,关于只有美国人能赢得这个奖杯的消息\NAs the only born American to win this cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.10,0:45:56.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想说  欢迎你们\NI'd Iike to say to you boys, welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.18,0:45:58.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我们对你们的到来感到很高兴  -听听\N- We're happy to have you. - Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.06,0:46:01.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们都知道哈利·瓦顿赢过这个比赛\NWe know Harry Vardon was winning Opens
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.10,0:46:03.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那是很久以前了  当我们还在呀呀学语时\Nback when most of us were Iearning our ABC's.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.74,0:46:08.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在这项运动的历史上  他是个天才\NHe's a genius in the history of our game.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.86,0:46:13.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,瓦顿先生  我知道  你在这项赛事成立的早期赢得过比赛\NMr. Vardon, I know you won this baby once before.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.14,0:46:15.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我在这里看到过你的名字\NI see your name here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.78,0:46:17.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是看起来那是很久以前的事了\NIt's a Iong time ago, by the Iook of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.22,0:46:24.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们希望你们能在波士顿过得愉快\NWell, we hope you boys have a nice time here in Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.78,0:46:27.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我个人认为  那不可能\NPersonally, I don't think you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.78,0:46:30.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我不关心在以后的六个星期  你们是否会大胜我们\NI don't care if you whupped us the Iast six weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.70,0:46:34.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我讨厌人们谈的都是你能赢比赛的消息\NI'm tired of people saying all you have to do to win is show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.50,0:46:37.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这次  你他妈的  不可能把这个杯给捧回去了\NThis time you're not taking our damn cup back!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.30,0:46:44.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,真想把那家伙给干掉\NMight just have to kill that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.06,0:46:47.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-祝你好运  先生  -谢谢你  先生\N- Good Iuck, sir. - Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.10,0:46:49.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,比利\NBilly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.74,0:46:51.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天早上见面如何  \NSee you first thing tomorrow morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.90,0:46:53.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-不行  -为什么  \N- I can't. - Well, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.02,0:46:56.41,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这个英国人出了20美元  如果他赢了的话  \NThis English fella offered me 20 bucks,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.41,0:46:57.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,会给我50美元\N50 if he wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.66,0:47:02.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我无法支付那样的价格\NWell, I can't give you anything Iike that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.78,0:47:05.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  弗朗西斯  我得回家照顾两个孩子\NI'm sorry, Francis. I've got two kids at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.82,0:47:14.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,坎贝尔先生  我的球童走了\NMr. Campbell? I just Iost my caddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.74,0:47:16.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你认识别的球童吗  \NDo you know somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.78,0:47:19.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-对不起  所有的都被雇完了  -那我该怎么办  \N- Sorry, all the Iads are taken. - What am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.66,0:47:21.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,自己解决问题  你认为瓦顿和雷\NHitch up your knickers. You think Vardon and Ray
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.06,0:47:24.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,会因为你自己背装备而同情你吗  \Nwill take pity because you carry your own bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.42,0:47:27.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是公开赛  每个人只为自己\NThis is the Open. Every man for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.26,0:47:31.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我该怎么办  \NWhat am I doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.02,0:47:36.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  弗朗西斯  \NHey, Francis!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.70,0:47:38.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,杰克  你来这儿做什么  \NJack! What are you doin' here?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.46,0:47:41.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我和埃迪翘课  过来看看练习赛\NMe and Eddie hooked school to come watch the practice round.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.58,0:47:43.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你还在富兰克林公园做球童吗  \NAre you still caddying out at Franklin Park?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.94,0:47:45.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-是的  -你能不能  \N- That's right. - Any chance you can
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.78,0:47:47.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天帮我当球童  \Ncarry for me tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.30,0:47:49.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-在公开赛上吗  -是的\N- In the Open? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.38,0:47:53.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你原来的那个球童怎么啦  \NWell, what happened to your guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.50,0:47:55.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他找到了个更好的雇主\NHe got a better offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.58,0:47:57.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,说明那个家伙是个大肥猪  对吗  \NThen that guy's a big, fat jerk! What?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.78,0:48:00.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,杰克  如果你愿意的话\NJack, if you're gonna do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.58,0:48:03.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天早上7:30之前到这儿来\Nyou gotta be here tomorrow at 7':30 sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.30,0:48:04.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快答应  \NDo it!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.54,0:48:06.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,埃迪能来吗  \NCan Eddie come too?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.70,0:48:08.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,杰克  我不能改变规则\NJack, I can't change the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.70,0:48:10.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只允许你一个人背包\NYou're only allowed one man on the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.98,0:48:19.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也许他能和我们一起  帮记记分数\NMaybe he could walk with us and keep score.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.74,0:48:21.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会解决的\NWe'II figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.62,0:48:24.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-可以吗  -好的\N- Is that OK with you? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.54,0:48:26.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  成交\NFrancis, you got yourself a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.38,0:48:28.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,太好了  杰克  太好了\NThat's great, Jack. That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.38,0:48:29.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,再见  埃迪\NI'II see ya, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.14,0:48:35.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我来开门  亨利  \NI'II get it, Henry!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.06,0:48:40.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你来做什么  \NAnd what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.66,0:48:43.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想和莎拉说句话  她在吗  \NI was hopin' to speak to Sarah. Is she here?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.14,0:48:45.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,她去上学了\NShe Ieft for college.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.42,0:48:48.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-什么时候  今天吗  -是的\N- When, today? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.54,0:48:52.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,帮我给她带个口信\NGive her a message for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.02,0:48:56.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是谁  弗雷迪\NWho was that, Freddie?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.38,0:48:59.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是  没什么人  只是个小贩\NAh, it was... it was no one. It was a peddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.38,0:49:01.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你听说过球童参加公开赛的事情吗  \NDid you hear about the caddie playing in the Open?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.90,0:49:05.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这种事从未发生过  各方面都异常关心\NIt should never have happened. Reflects badly on all concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.26,0:49:07.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,照我说  没有什么比\NI say, if he wants to go out and play
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.26,0:49:09.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让他比赛丢丑更好的了\Nand make a fool of himself again, so much the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.98,0:49:12.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你们在谈论谁  -是俱乐部的事情\N- Who are you talking about? - It's a club matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.98,0:49:14.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,球童\NCaddie Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.62,0:49:16.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特\NOuimet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.18,0:49:19.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,还坚持说他是个业余选手  这个世界怎么啦  \NInsists he's an amateur. What is the world coming to?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.98,0:49:23.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-再要些汤吗  先生  -好的  哈利\N- More bisque, sir? - Thank you, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.46,0:49:26.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥德丽今晚为我们准备了什么派  \NAnd what kind of pie does Audrey have for us tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.78,0:49:30.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-越橘派  先生  -太好了\N- Huckleberry, sir. - Ah. Splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.06,0:49:42.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你以为能一直瞒着我  \NDid you think you could keep it from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.06,0:49:45.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我从未试过\NI didn't try to.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.26,0:49:48.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你的名字出现在报纸上了  总是背着我做\NYour name is in the newspaper, sneaking around behind my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.66,0:49:50.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是的  爸爸\NNo, no, no, Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.30,0:49:52.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须停下来\NYou're going to stop this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.54,0:49:56.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一个男人应该知道自己的位置  并且静下心去做\NA man knows his place and makes his peace with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.34,0:49:58.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我不想谈这个  -那你就听着吧\N- I can't talk about this. - Then you Iisten.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.94,0:50:01.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是为你好\NThis is for your own good.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.34,0:50:03.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我试图保护你\NI am trying to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.18,0:50:04.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,保护我什么  \NProtect me from what?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.86,0:50:08.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  那些人  不需要在世上找自己的位子\NFrancis, those men don't have to earn a place in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.98,0:50:10.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是他们的世界\NIt's given to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.50,0:50:13.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是我们这些人的\NWe're not those kind of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.58,0:50:16.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你现在去告诉他们  你不参赛了\NNow, you go tell them that you can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.78,0:50:18.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就说这只是个错误\NIt's a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.78,0:50:23.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我不会这么做的\NI won't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.10,0:50:29.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你答应过我的\NYou gave me your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.74,0:50:33.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你答应过我的\NYou gave me your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.58,0:50:35.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我现在不能放弃  对不起\NI can't quit now. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.86,0:50:41.86,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那就帮我个忙  当这一切结束后\NThen so help me, when this is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.94,0:50:45.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你自己找个其他的地方住吧\Nyou find somewhere else to Iive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.90,0:51:00.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好的\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.26,0:51:24.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你确信这些人都受过礼仪教育\NMake sure these people get the etiquette guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.74,0:51:27.34,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们大多数人  以前都没有参加高尔夫课程\NMost of them have never been on a golf course before.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.42,0:51:29.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪\NGod help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.46,0:51:31.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特先生\NMr. Ouimet!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.70,0:51:33.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特先生\NMr. Ouimet!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.78,0:51:39.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,埃迪  \NEddie!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.66,0:51:41.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,杰克在哪儿  我等了他10分钟了\NWhere's Jack? I tee off in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.74,0:51:43.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他被逮着了  现在在学校\NTruant officer caught him. He's in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.98,0:51:47.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-为什么你没有和他在一起  -天哪  这可是美国公开赛\N- Why aren't you with him? - Come on! This is the U.S. Open.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.14,0:51:48.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢你过来告诉我\NThanks for coming to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.86,0:51:51.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特先生  我可以为你当球童\NMr. Ouimet, I can caddie for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.74,0:51:54.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,埃迪  我的包和你一样高\NEddie, my bag is as big as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.58,0:51:55.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我可以做到\NBut I can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.06,0:51:58.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在富兰克林公园  我帮很多人背过包  你去问问\NI carry for Iots of fellas at Franklin Park. Ask 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.86,0:52:01.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我能做得和杰克一样好\NI came to make good on what Jack promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.10,0:52:04.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我从学校逃课  坐了3辆电车  我够高了\NI hooked school, took three streetcars and I am big enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.78,0:52:07.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我5年级了  我想为你当球童\NI'm in 5th grade, and I want to caddie for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.34,0:52:09.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,先安静一下\NCalm down for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.30,0:52:12.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这样如何  我背包  你跟着我\NHow about this? I'II carry my bag, and you walk next to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.70,0:52:14.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-不行  奥密特先生  -叫我弗朗西斯\N- No, Mr. Ouimet! - Call me Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.54,0:52:16.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我能办到  奥密特先生  -叫我弗朗西斯\N- I can do it, Mr. Ouimet. - Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.54,0:52:18.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道你的名字  我看过你的比赛\NI know your game. I've seen you play.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.74,0:52:21.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我可以背那个包  -好吧  好吧\N- I can carry that bag! - AII right. AII right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.30,0:52:25.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以当我的球童  好吗  但是你必须叫我弗朗西斯\NYou can caddie for me. OK? But you're gonna have to call me Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.62,0:52:28.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-好的  弗朗西斯  -好吧\N- OK, Francis. - AII right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.78,0:52:34.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你们有毛病吗  \NYou got a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.90,0:52:37.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,现在是9:45  开球时间\NThis is the 9:45 tee time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.38,0:52:39.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,卡托沃基高尔夫俱乐部的\NThe professional from Cattawaukee Golf CIub,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.86,0:52:41.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,阿尔伯特·莫里\NAIbert Murray.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.78,0:52:48.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,来自马萨诸塞州布鲁克莱恩的\NFrom Brookline, Massachusetts,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.66,0:52:51.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,业余选手弗朗西斯·奥密特\Namateur Mr. Francis Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.06,0:53:46.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不管你决定做什么  弗朗西斯\NWhatever you decide, Francis,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.98,0:53:49.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,冷静下来  我会看着球的\Nkeep your head down and I'II watch the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.26,0:53:50.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们肯定能打进那个洞\NWe're gonna par this hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.86,0:54:15.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就该这样  打好每一球\NThat's the stuff. One shot at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.18,0:54:33.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只需要轻轻一击就解决了\NOne putt, we'II get that par.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.70,0:54:35.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,现在就是要细心  稳定\NNice and steady now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.50,0:54:37.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让球滚动  就能进洞\NMake it roll, it'II seek the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.78,0:54:57.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,太容易了\NEasy peazy, Iemon squeezy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.18,0:55:53.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他不可能打不进的\NHe's not supposed to miss those.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.18,0:55:54.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,今天早上的第三个了\NThird one this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.66,0:55:57.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他到底怎么了  \NWhat the devil's wrong with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.34,0:55:59.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我确实不知道  先生\NI'm sure I don't know, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.70,0:56:49.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,打到树林里去了  你们这帮蠢货\NIt's in the bleedin' trees, you great bunch o' ninnies.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.38,0:56:52.98,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,特德  你运气真差啊  老伙计  \NTed! Rotten Iuck, old boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.06,0:56:56.74,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-才是第一天  感觉如何  -还有很多高尔夫赛要打\N- Just one of those days, what? - Still a Iot of golf to play yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.46,0:57:00.22,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,势利小人\NToffee-nosed git.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.74,0:57:12.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,有两类选手\NThere are only two types of player:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.38,0:57:15.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一类是绷着神经要赢比赛\NThose who keep their nerves in control and win championships,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.66,0:57:17.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一类却相反\Nand those who do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.34,0:57:44.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  弗朗西斯  那个大块头是谁  \NHey, Francis, who's that big, fat guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.10,0:57:49.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  天哪  是塔夫脱总统\NOh, my gosh. It's President T aft.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.22,0:57:51.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,瞎扯  是塔夫脱总统吗  \NGet out! President T aft?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.98,0:57:54.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是美国总统塔夫脱吗  \NThe United States President T aft?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.58,0:57:57.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你以前见过总统吗  -第一次\N- You ever seen a president before? - First time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.74,0:58:00.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  总统先生  你在那儿做什么  \NHey! How you doin' there, Mr. President?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.66,0:58:07.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  刚才的最后一洞你打出小鸟球吗  \NFrancis! Did you just birdie your Iast hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.38,0:58:09.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想是的  弗兰克\NI guess I did, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.14,0:58:11.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪  弗朗西斯  你紧跟在瓦顿之后\NHoly smokes, Francis, you're tied with Vardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.78,0:58:14.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你是第二名  -我吗  \N- You're in second place. - I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.14,0:58:17.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,塔夫脱总统在谈论你  是塔夫脱总统啊\NPresident Taft is talking about you. President Taft.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.02,0:58:19.46,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,很难相信是吧  \NIsn't it incredible?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.54,0:58:21.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  伙计们  我们有工作\NOK, we're working here, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.58,0:58:23.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不要听他们的\NDon't Iisten to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.10,0:58:25.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们打我们的比赛  让那些人去为他们的事情烦心吧\NWe play our game, Iet those guys worry about theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.66,0:58:30.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我紧跟在  \NI'm tied...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.22,0:58:43.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你跟在Vardan后面  你是第二名\NYou're tied with Vardon. You're in second place.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.38,0:58:55.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  天哪\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.26,0:59:34.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的\NThanks for nothin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.42,1:00:02.54,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们得冷静一下  弗朗西斯\NWe gotta settle down now, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.62,1:00:04.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  是吗  我们该怎么做  \NOh, yeah? How are we gonna do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.10,1:00:08.10,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你应该打得更好\NYou're just gonna have to play better.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.10,1:00:11.58,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让自己冷静下来\NKeep your head down.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.26,1:00:54.82,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好吧  给我5号铁头球棍\NAII right, gimme the mashie.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.86,1:00:56.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你不该用这支球棍\NYou're not gonna reach with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.70,1:00:57.94,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他可以  我就可以\NIf he can, I can.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.50,1:01:27.14,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在第二轮  哈利·瓦顿拉开了\NIn round two, Harry Vardon's pulled even
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.22,1:01:29.62,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,与防守方冠军约翰·麦克德莫特  的差距\Nwith the defending champion, John McDermott,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.70,1:01:34.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是威尔弗雷德·里德先生  却一杆一杆的追赶上来\Nbut Mr. Wilfred Reid is matching him shot for shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.38,1:01:36.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,经过一个早上的糟糕表现\NAfter a poor showing this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.46,1:01:39.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,特德·雷看上去  就像个被围困的疯狂野兽\NTed Ray's stalking the grounds Iike a mad brute.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.46,1:01:42.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他  疯狂野兽\NHe... Mad brute.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.90,1:01:46.06,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也许他在这场锦标赛  还有点希望\NHe may yet have something to say about this championship.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.14,1:01:57.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,安静\NQuiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.94,1:02:12.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,继续  继续  继续  \NGo, go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.34,1:02:13.42,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,进去\NGet in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.38,1:02:20.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哎呀\NBIimey.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.82,1:02:23.50,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们太容易激动了\NThey're easily entertained.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.58,1:02:25.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我就指望你了  老伙计\NI'm counting on you, old boy,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.34,1:02:27.90,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,瓦顿和那粗野的家伙  恐怕没法赢\Nif Vardon and that great ape of his can't deliver.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.98,1:02:30.02,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上  都是为了英格兰\NQuite. AII for England.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.10,1:02:32.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,收起那些对报纸说的  冠冕堂皇的话\NSave that patriotic gibberish for the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.86,1:02:35.70,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,总理答应我说  如果带回这个奖杯\NThe prime minister has promised me a seat in his cabinet
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.78,1:02:37.18,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就让我进入内阁\Nif I bring back this trophy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.26,1:02:40.30,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,果真如此  我会记得你的  威尔弗雷德\NAnd rest assured, Wilfred, you will be remembered.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.86,1:02:43.66,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,啊  打的好啊  哈利\NAh. Bravo, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.74,1:02:45.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你领先我一点\NYou're tied with me for the Iead.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.46,1:02:49.38,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你打的很好  先生  -为了国王和国家  如何  \N- Very well played, sir. - AII for King and country, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.46,1:02:52.78,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,威尔弗雷德打的很出色  比你带来的那个雷好多了\NWilfred played splendidly, more than can be said for your man Ray.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.86,1:02:54.26,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他就像个野蛮人\NWild as a Hottentot.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.36,1:02:57.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然他在第一轮里表现不俗  但他不可能在淘汰赛中胜出\NAfter his appalling first round, he won't survive the cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.76,1:03:01.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们究竟在做什么  \NWhat on earth are they going on about?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.88,1:03:04.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,特德·雷刚刚打破了得分记录\NTed Ray's just broken the course scoring record.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.76,1:03:09.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天啊  雷紧跟在第二\NBy Jove, Ray's tied for second!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.96,1:03:23.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特先生  能问个问题吗  \NMr. Ouimet? One question, sir!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.20,1:03:25.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯\NFrancis!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.20,1:03:28.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  我以为你回学校了  \NHey! I thought you'd gone back to college!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.16,1:03:31.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我还以为你放弃比赛了  -我改变主意了  不是吗  \N- I thought you quit playing! - I guess I changed my mind, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.32,1:03:33.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-真是太好了  -是的\N- That's wonderful! - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.12,1:03:35.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,很高兴能见到你  你明天能来吗  \NIt's great to see you. Can you come tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.56,1:03:38.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-我明天得走了  -明天来吧\N- I have to Ieave tomorrow! - Come back tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.68,1:03:47.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你是他的球童吗  \NAre you his caddie?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.12,1:03:51.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,把这个给他  好吗  \NGive this to him, would you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.56,1:03:55.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,幸运符\NFor Iuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.68,1:04:04.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这种东西谁需要啊  \NDames. Who needs 'em?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.56,1:04:24.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,今天打得不错啊  奥密特先生\NFine play today, Mr. Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.32,1:04:26.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢  先生  你也打得很好\NThank you, sir. You too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.12,1:04:30.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我只是运气好而已\NIt's mostly dumb Iuck, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.60,1:04:35.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,运气只是对我而言的\NOn my part. Not on your part.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.48,1:04:37.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你不需要运气  而我却需要\NYou don't need Iuck. I need Iuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.00,1:04:42.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嗯  那祝你好运\NWell, good Iuck, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.80,1:04:44.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢你  先生\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.28,1:04:56.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我把它们都擦干净了  连手柄也擦了\NI cleaned 'em good. Wiped the grips too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.80,1:05:00.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你今天真是做的太棒了\NYou did just fine out there today.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.56,1:05:02.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你也一样  弗朗西斯\NYou too, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.08,1:05:04.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你明天还能逃出来吗  \NYou gonna be able to skip school again tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.84,1:05:06.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让他们试试看能不能阻止我\NLet 'em try and stop me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.60,1:05:09.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那好  路上小心\NAII right, well, you get home safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.32,1:05:11.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  你不用担心我\NHey, don't you worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.24,1:05:12.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天一大早\NI'II meet you right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.84,1:05:14.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我会在这里等你的\NEarly bird gets the worm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.44,1:05:15.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一言为定\NDeal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.32,1:05:40.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,小姐们  我只能说  当比赛开始时\NAII I can say, Iadies, is that when the day began,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.12,1:05:42.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我简直没法想象\NI scarcely imagined that I'd find myself
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.44,1:05:45.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我竟然能紧跟在  伟大的哈利·瓦顿之后\Ntied for the Iead with the immortal Harry Vardon,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.24,1:05:48.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,并且领先曾经的王者特德·雷两杆\Nand two strokes ahead of the ever-so-capable Ted Ray.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.92,1:05:52.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,啊  说曹操  曹操就到\NAh. Speak of the devil, and up he pops.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.12,1:05:54.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  小姐们  我要离开一会儿\NExcuse me, Iadies. I'II be with you presently.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.12,1:06:02.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我简直是太喜欢美国妞了\NI simply adore Americans.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.12,1:06:06.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,活力四射  那么的迷人  那么的天真\NThe exuberance, such charming naiveté.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.28,1:06:08.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你是怎么找到她们的  特德  \NHow do you find them, Ted?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.76,1:06:11.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我想你在家一定很在行\NI should imagine you feel right at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.64,1:06:15.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,她们有一大堆礼节要遵从  却又渴望有人挤压她们的大胸脯\NThey clasp all manner of the huddled, yearning masses to their bosoms.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.36,1:06:18.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至是低级的高尔夫选手\NEven the Iowly golf professional.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.24,1:06:20.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道吗  我可以预言\NYou know, I can foresee a day,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.44,1:06:23.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,当他们邀请你们这类人去俱乐部时\Ngiven their democratic standards,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.48,1:06:26.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,肯定是和你们谈民主问题\Nwhen they invite your kind into their clubhouses.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.64,1:06:28.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  他们如何忍受得了  \NWell, how could they resist?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.76,1:06:31.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,从泽西岛来的两个可怜家伙  还是白手起家的\NTwo poor Iads from Jersey, up from nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.96,1:06:34.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,从工人阶级到平民百姓\NWorking-class heroes to the great unwashed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.00,1:06:36.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,泽西岛曾经只是\NWhen all Jersey's ever given us
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.84,1:06:39.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,提供我们马铃薯和奶牛  \Nare potatoes and dairy cows...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.04,1:06:44.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不要看\NDon't Iook over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.88,1:06:47.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起  哈利  我没法控制自己\NSorry, Harry. I couldn't contain myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.04,1:06:49.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他也一样\NNeither could he.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.84,1:06:52.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他不应该把泽西岛也牵扯进来\NHe shouldn't have brought Jersey into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.92,1:07:02.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,上帝啊  我的鼻子\NMy God. My nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.92,1:07:08.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我看起来还好吧  \NDo I Iook all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.68,1:07:12.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,说的非常坦诚  里德先生  有了进步\NQuite frankly, Mr. Reid, it's an improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.00,1:07:19.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那么  你真的见到总统了  \NSo, did you really see the President?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.48,1:07:20.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他向我挥手了\NHe waved at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.88,1:07:21.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不可能\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.96,1:07:23.89,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,真的  塔夫脱总统真的是做了  \NYes, he did. President Taft.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.90,1:07:25.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你能相信弗朗西斯吗\NCan you believe Francis?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.12,1:07:27.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,今晚我睡楼下如何  \NWhy don't I sleep downstairs tonight?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.24,1:07:28.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不  你睡楼上\NNo. You sleep upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.88,1:07:31.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-为了明天的比赛  你需要好的睡眠  -我没事\N- You'II need your sleep for tomorrow. - I'm OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.96,1:07:33.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  亚瑟  \NOh! Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.64,1:07:41.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们称呼你奥密特先生\NSo, they call you Mr. Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.84,1:07:45.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,而对其他人则直呼其名\NThe others, it just says their names.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.24,1:07:49.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,爸爸  他们是职业选手\NWell, Father, they're professionals.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.36,1:07:51.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我只是个业余的\NI'm an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.32,1:07:52.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,吃点甜点吧\NLet's have some dessert.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.72,1:07:54.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不用  等等  坐下来\NNo, wait, wait. Sit, sit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.40,1:07:58.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,现在他们都在谈论你\NThey're all talking about you now.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.00,1:08:05.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,说就算你赢了  也得不到奖金\NIt say here that if you win, you get no money.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.52,1:08:08.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,其他人有奖金  你却什么也没有\NThe others make money, you get nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.68,1:08:10.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这说明了什么  \NWhat does that prove?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.28,1:08:14.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这说明了什么  \NWhat does that prove?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.76,1:08:19.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们甚至都不给你工资  这是个什么工作  \NThey don't even pay you! What kind of work is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.32,1:08:20.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-亚瑟  -干吗  \N- Arthur. - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.76,1:08:22.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我给你拿盘子来\NI'II fix you a plate.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.40,1:09:11.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快点  用力拉  \NCome on, you! Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.56,1:09:29.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,早上好  哈利\NMorning, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.32,1:09:32.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,讨厌的英国式天气\NDreadful English weather.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.12,1:09:38.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-睡得怎么样  -就像个婴儿\N- How'd you sleep? - Like a baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.48,1:09:41.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,过两个小时就要醒来并且哭闹\NWoke up every two hours and cried.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.56,1:09:58.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  弗朗西斯\NHey, Francis!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.08,1:10:01.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我昨晚梦见你打出了72杆的好成绩  \NI had a dream Iast night that you shot a 72!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.08,1:10:03.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,真的  在风暴中要打出来可不容易\NYeah? It won't be easy in a nor'easter.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.56,1:10:06.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你可是在这种天气中打出过的\NYou've played this course in weather Iike this.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.56,1:10:08.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你说的对  这是个打出72杆的好日子\NYou're right. It's a good day for a 72.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.52,1:10:10.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好耶\NOkeydokey, pipe and smokey.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.80,1:10:45.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果英国人赢了我们  他们会说我以前只是侥幸赢的\NIf the Brits beat us, they'II say it was a fluke I ever won it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.12,1:10:48.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们会说这是他们的比赛  我们还不够格\NThey'II say it's their game, and we're not good enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.16,1:10:49.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我们的公开赛\NThis is our Open.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.56,1:13:20.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  真不可思议\NYes. Marvelous.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.28,1:13:32.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特  奥密特  奥-密-特\NOuimet. Ouimet. O-U-I-M-E-T.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.04,1:13:36.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,三轮过后他只是比瓦顿和雷落后一杆\NHe's only one stroke behind Vardon and Ray after three rounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.16,1:13:40.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,移走它  用背去顶\NMove it! Put your backs into it now!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.84,1:13:45.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,再挖深些  我们走\NGo a Iittle deeper there! There we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.20,1:13:53.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不在这  去那边看看\NNot here. Over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.32,1:13:55.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好好检查一下尽头\NWatch that end go through!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.48,1:13:58.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-往下放  -好的  先生\N- And move on down! - Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.84,1:14:34.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.44,1:14:43.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,雷只需轻轻一击就处于领先了\NRay needs that putt for the Iead.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.44,1:14:45.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我不想听别人是怎么做的\NI don't want to hear how anyone else is doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.84,1:14:48.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们打我们的球\NWe play our own game.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.60,1:14:51.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们现在处在什么位置  \NWhere do we stand?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.72,1:14:55.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你得用标准杆数通过最后5个洞  才能追上特德  处于领先\NYou'd still have to par the Iast five holes to tie Ted for the Iead.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.64,1:14:57.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,形势很糟糕  哈利\NDreadful conditions, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.44,1:14:59.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,没有人会指责你  如果你  \NNo one would blame you if you came...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.32,1:15:00.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢  伯纳德\NThank you, Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.60,1:16:53.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,球进水里了  他完了\NHe's done for in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.04,1:16:56.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他不可能追上了\NNo chance he catches him now.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.88,1:17:43.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么啦  伙计  \NWhat's got into you, old thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.08,1:17:45.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,别过来惹我烦\NYou had to go and get me angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.28,1:17:47.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  是我的错\NOh, yes. My mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.28,1:17:49.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,打完这个\NWhen I par this one,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.28,1:17:51.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就得尽全力去打明天的\Nwe'II have to go at it again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.24,1:17:53.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,决赛吗  真讨厌\NA playoff? What a bother.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.32,1:17:55.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  但是必须\NYes, but there it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.80,1:17:58.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,以前从没有看见过  你比赛的时候抽烟\NNever seen you smoke on the job before.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.12,1:18:00.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只是提前了4个洞的时间而已\NShould've started four holes earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.04,1:18:55.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,没有什么好担心的了\NAh, all square again.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.48,1:18:58.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这个年轻人没有机会赶超了\NNot a chance this stripling bears up.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.36,1:19:00.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也许不是这样的\NProbably not.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.28,1:19:30.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让他们看\NLet 'em Iook.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.52,1:19:32.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们这些紧跟着的  就只有你还在打了\NWe're tied, and you're the one still playing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.60,1:19:51.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,最好能避开这种英国式的恶劣天气\NMight as well get out of this beastly New England weather
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.60,1:19:53.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,举杯庆祝英国的胜利吧\Nand raise a glass to British victory.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.68,1:19:56.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谁在给他扛包  是个侏儒吗  \NWhat's that carrying his bag, a Pygmy?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.32,1:20:10.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们需要两杆  一杆这儿  另一杆在16洞\NWe need two strokes. One here, one at the 1 6th...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.44,1:20:13.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,弗朗西斯  别想那么多  你不可能一下子把他们拿下来\NFrancis, don't think so much. You can't play 'em all at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.76,1:20:15.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一个一个地打\NYou gotta take 'em one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.40,1:20:18.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,每次一杆  要两杆  要两杆  六个洞\NOne at a time, two down. Two down, six to play.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.40,1:20:20.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我可以在这里得一杆  在16洞得一杆\NI can get one here and another on 1 6.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.52,1:20:22.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那个女孩让我把这个交给你\NThat girl wanted me to give you this.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.76,1:20:25.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-哪个女孩  -莎拉\N- What girl? - Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.28,1:20:26.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,莎拉给你的  \NSarah gave you this?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.00,1:20:29.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你就戴上吧  别让它淋湿了\NJust put it on. Don't get all sloppy over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.40,1:20:41.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,为了英国\NTo England.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.12,1:20:45.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那究竟是怎么回事  \NWhat the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.60,1:20:47.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一切还没有结束\NIt's not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.20,1:21:16.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  哦  瞧  谁回来了\NWell, well. Look who's back.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.60,1:21:46.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-很好  -打得不错\N- Nice. - Nice shot!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.60,1:21:51.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让我们过去  这是奥密特的母亲\NLet us through. It's Ouimet's mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.20,1:22:00.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,情况怎么样啦  \NWhat's happenin'?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.04,1:22:03.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他在16洞这里思考\NHe hit it stone dead at 1 6.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.92,1:22:05.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他只有一杆的机会\NHe's only down one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.44,1:22:09.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,什么意思  这是好事情吗  \NWhat does that mean? Is it good?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.80,1:22:12.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他做到了  就会进决赛\NIf he makes this, it's a playoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.16,1:22:15.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪  这几乎超越了人的计算能力\NDear me, it's almost beyond one's ability to calculate.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.56,1:22:18.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,啊  请别介意  我喝口酒\NAh, don't mind if I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.96,1:22:28.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他不可能成功的  不可能\NHe can't keep this up. It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.80,1:23:37.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的\NI'II be damned.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.04,1:23:45.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,哦  弗朗西斯  \NOh, Francis!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.20,1:24:09.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天瓦顿  雷和奥密特先生\NThere will be an 1 8-hole playoff tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.16,1:24:12.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,将进行18洞的比赛\Nbetween Vardon, Ray and Mr. Ouimet
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.48,1:24:14.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,决出冠军\Nto decide the Championship.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.24,1:24:28.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这个男孩是上帝给的礼物\NThat boy's a gift from the gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.92,1:24:31.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,国内正在夜以继日的印刷\NThey're printing 'round the clock at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.44,1:24:33.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪  猜猜他们能在这儿卖什么\NCripes! Imagine what they're selling here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.84,1:24:36.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果有机会  我是不是该买块烂抹布\NShould have bought one of these rags when I had the chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.84,1:24:42.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他敢于站出来  但是他会受到重创的\NIt's a bold charge, but he's spent his powder.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.36,1:24:45.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,伙计们  这是两个人的比赛\NIt's a two-man game now, my Iads.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.16,1:24:47.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,英国人的决赛\NAn all-English final.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.88,1:24:50.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嗯  我们得看看\NWell, we'II see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.56,1:24:53.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  哈利  真难以想象\NCome on, Harry. It's inconceivable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.52,1:24:57.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那个人居然是个该死的业余选手\NThe man's a bloody amateur.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.52,1:24:59.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你上一次被击败  是什么时候  \NWhen was the Iast time you were beaten...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.92,1:25:01.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在男人和男人的对决中\NHave you ever been beaten, man-to-man,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.00,1:25:04.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在你的职业生涯中  你有被业余选手打败过吗  \Nin your entire career by an amateur?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.36,1:25:06.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,业余选手是不可能赢得公开赛的\NAmateurs do not win Opens.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.60,1:25:09.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的  最近一个赢得比赛的\NHell, the Iast one who won it back home
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.08,1:25:11.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也是40年前了  而且他是个绅士\Nwas 40 years ago, and he was a gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.24,1:25:14.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,而这个人  他什么也不是  他只是个农民  一个土老冒\NThis one's nothing of the kind. He's a peasant. Common clay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.76,1:25:17.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他会被打得惨败的\NHe'II fold Iike an accordion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.20,1:25:19.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我需要休息一下\NI need my rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.20,1:25:27.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他不能把球击出一英里  他将只是个挖沟的\NIf he couldn't hit the ball a country mile, he'd be digging ditches.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.68,1:25:35.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你去哪儿  哈利  坐下来吧\NWhere are you going, Harry? Sit down with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.28,1:25:38.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,和我一起吃  放松一下自己\NEat with me. Enjoy yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.20,1:25:40.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我来这是为了赢比赛\NI came here to win a trophy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.32,1:25:42.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是说  我和特德·雷能自己应对\NOn the face of it, Ted Ray or I should carry it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.96,1:25:44.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是为了你  也不是为了英国\NNot for you, not for England,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.92,1:25:48.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只是为了成为最好的那份荣誉  这就是我们打比赛的原因\Nbut for bloody pride at being the best. That's why we do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.08,1:25:51.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果明天奥密特先生赢得比赛的话  那是因为他是最棒的\NAnd if Mr. Ouimet wins tomorrow, it's because he's the best,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.84,1:25:54.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是因为他本人\Nbecause of who he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.20,1:25:56.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不管他父亲是谁  也不管他有没有钱\NNot who his father was, not how much money he's got,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.00,1:25:58.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只是因为他本人\Nbecause of who he bloody is!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.04,1:26:02.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我希望你记住\NAnd I'II thank you to remember that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.64,1:26:08.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我还要感谢你  做为一位绅士所应当表现出来的尊敬\NAnd I'II thank you to show the respect a gentleman gives as a matter of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.88,1:26:11.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,晚安\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.56,1:26:39.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你想他输掉  是吗  \NDo you want him to fail?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.96,1:26:44.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这样你才会安心  是吗  \NIs that the only satisfaction you can take from what he's doin'?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.44,1:26:50.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,难道你认为我会让他伤心  \NYou think I want him to break his heart?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.56,1:26:56.04,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,玛丽  如果他输了  你会怎么做  \NWhat will you do, Mary, when he fails?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.16,1:26:58.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,到时候  你如何帮他  \NHow will you help him then?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.24,1:27:01.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你所能做的只是鼓励他\NAII you ever do is encourage him.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.20,1:27:07.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是的  我就是鼓励他\NThat's right. I do encourage him.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.92,1:27:10.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他有天赋\NHe has a God-given talent,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.00,1:27:13.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是他的一个机会  能展现他的才能\Nand this is his one chance to give a voice to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.48,1:27:19.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他只是想让你感到自豪\NHe's just tryin' to make you proud.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.04,1:27:51.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,真难以置信  这个没有经过训练的男孩\N"It seems impossible to believe that this untested boy
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.64,1:27:54.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,居然有希望  打败两位经验丰富的冠军选手\Ncould hope to beat two seasoned champions."
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.52,1:28:02.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,一个凡人对付两个巨人\NOne David against two Goliaths.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.64,1:28:08.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天  在让人难以置信的场合\NHe'll have to face Vardon and Ray alone,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.32,1:28:10.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他将独自面对瓦顿和雷\Nwith a night to sleep on the incredible situation
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.04,1:28:14.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他会发现一个非常不一样的自我\Nin which he so shockingly finds himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.60,1:28:18.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然\NAlthough, I suspect,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.44,1:28:21.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我对他今天所表现出来的异常冷静  表示怀疑\Nfrom the unearthly calm he showed today,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.20,1:28:23.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是他会睡得比平时都好\Nhe will sleep better than most.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.08,1:28:29.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我不是很确定奥密特能赢\NI am not certain I believe Ouimet can win,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.52,1:28:33.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我放弃去预测的想法\Nbut I have given up all attempts at prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.68,1:28:37.88,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,明天的比赛  我将公平对待\NI will start tomorrow's round with an open mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.08,1:28:43.40,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这将是最伟大的比赛\NIt should be the greatest game ever played.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.76,1:28:51.97,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,美国公开赛  第三天  决赛
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.52,1:29:22.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,年轻人  我们得商量一下\NYoung man. We've been talking this over.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.28,1:29:23.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,商量什么  \NT alking what over?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.72,1:29:27.44,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,委员们认为  今天你会需要很多的帮助\NThe members feel you need as much help as you can get out there today.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.52,1:29:29.80,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-什么帮助  -依据规则  \N- What kind of help? - According to the rules,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.88,1:29:32.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只有你的球童能给你出主意\Nyour caddie is the only person who can give you advice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.68,1:29:36.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,今天你需要一个  真正懂得我们的规则的人\NYou need someone with you today who really knows our course.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.28,1:29:39.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-是的  -埃迪做得很好\N- Exactly. - Eddie's doin' a great job for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.20,1:29:40.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪  奥密特  \NFor God's sake, Ouimet!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.76,1:29:42.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这可是美国公开赛\NThis is the U.S. Open,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.36,1:29:44.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不是低级的俱乐部赛\Nnot some junior club championship.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.00,1:29:47.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在和我谈之前  你跟埃迪说了这件事情吗  \NYou told Eddie this before talking to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.24,1:29:49.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你不用向那种孩子解释\NOh, you can't reason with a boy Iike that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.40,1:29:52.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会让他退出  并给他一笔钱\NWe'II take up a collection for him and pay him handsomely.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.72,1:29:54.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他的家人应该会需要\NI understand his family could use it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.00,1:29:56.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不要让他们这么做  弗朗西斯  \NDon't Iet 'em do it, Francis!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.76,1:30:01.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你确定吗  你知道的  我可没有钱给你  埃迪\NIs it true? You know I can't pay you, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.28,1:30:04.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我不会为了10元钱来做的  我也不会为了100元来做\NI wouldn't do it for ten bucks. I wouldn't do it for a hundred!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.44,1:30:06.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿  听着  你认为我会替换掉你  是吗  \NHey, Iisten. You think I'd replace you?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.68,1:30:08.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,但是他们说你想这么做\NBut they said you'd want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.72,1:30:11.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,谁会去管他们的想法呢  谁会去关心呢  \NWho cares what they said? Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.16,1:30:14.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,只有你和我  我们是个团队  不是吗  \NThis is me and you. We're a team. OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.92,1:30:17.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们没有权利\NThey don't get a vote in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.20,1:30:18.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,好了吗  \NAII right?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.12,1:30:21.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你在外面等我\NI'II meet you outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.68,1:30:32.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,不要再和我的球童讨论这件事\NDon't ever talk to my caddie again.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.16,1:30:49.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,奥密特先生先打\NMr. Ouimet will play first.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.76,1:30:55.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,达尔文先生是记分员  负责记录你们的得分\NMr. Darwin will act as honorary marker and keep your scores.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.96,1:31:01.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,先生们  时间到了\NGentlemen, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.88,1:31:11.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-他出来了  -祝你好运  孩子\N- Here he comes! - Good Iuck, son!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.52,1:31:17.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-加油  年轻人  -加油  奥密特  \N- Come on, young man! - Come on, Ouimet!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.44,1:31:19.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,加油  弗朗西斯  加油\NCome on, Francis! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.96,1:31:28.12,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,给我们一个惊喜  孩子\NGive us a strong show, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.32,1:32:36.64,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-在那你得了5分是吗  -是的\N- Five for you there? - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.12,1:32:41.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你能赢  弗朗西斯\NYou can do it, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.04,1:32:42.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-什么  -嗯  对不起\N- What? - Wha... Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.64,1:32:44.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我刚才有说话吗  \NDid I say something?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.92,1:32:46.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,厉害\NThat was big.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.40,1:33:03.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他们也是凡人\NThey're human.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.84,1:33:05.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,什么  \NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.40,1:33:07.28,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我能打败他们  埃迪\NI can play these guys, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.36,1:33:09.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,是啊  谁说你不能了  \NYeah? Who said you couldn't?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.68,1:33:26.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,也许他们根本就不是人\NMaybe they're not human.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.96,1:33:38.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是他上次输了的地方\NThis is where he fell apart the Iast time.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.00,1:33:49.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,那是昨天的事情了\NThat was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.48,1:34:06.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,莎拉  \NSarah!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.80,1:34:09.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你在这干什么  你应该待在学校\NWhat are you doing here? You're supposed to be in school.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.80,1:34:11.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,别无聊了  爸爸\NDon't be ridiculous, Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.40,1:34:18.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他不是很优秀  哈利\NHe's not cracking, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.68,1:34:20.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我也是这么想的\NThe thought occurred to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.56,1:34:23.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,英国人自己的比赛\N"An all-English final."
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.56,1:34:35.24,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,请安静\NQuiet, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.32,1:35:10.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,该死的\NStymied.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.40,1:35:26.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-你做什么  -瞧我的\N- What are you doin'? - I'II show you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.96,1:35:51.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,快点  结束他\NCome on, now. Finish him.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.40,1:35:57.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,让我们看看他会不会崩溃\NLet's see if he cracks now.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.08,1:36:09.84,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,前面右边的注意\NFore right!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.28,1:36:17.68,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,他会被这些树阻挡完蛋的\NHe's dead in those trees.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.68,1:36:34.92,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,中号铁棍\NMid iron.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.52,1:36:57.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,在树林中结束了\NDone in by the monarch of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.40,1:37:25.00,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,该你了  老家伙  我结束了\NDown to you, old thing. I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.08,1:37:27.08,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,有些遗憾  不过这是重大的比赛\NPity. It's a great match.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.96,1:37:30.32,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,就是这种精神  哈利\NThat's the spirit, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.92,1:37:35.48,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,加油  奥密特\NCome on, Ouimet.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.84,1:40:22.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,你准备打去哪  \NWhere you going with that?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.64,1:40:25.36,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,-穿过拐角  -那儿有个沙坑\N- Gonna cut the corner. - There's a bunker down there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.44,1:40:27.20,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他打过去  就只需要推杆了\NIf he's over it, he's a chip away.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.24,1:40:29.52,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,我们不知道他是不是打过去了  这是个圈套\NWe don't know he's over it. It's a trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.44,1:41:37.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我们的机会  弗朗西斯\NThis is our chance, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.64,1:41:39.72,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,象昨天一样打到那儿\NRun it in there, just Iike yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.20,1:43:37.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,天哪  弗朗西斯领先了一杆\NMy God. Francis has a one-stroke Iead with one to play.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.84,1:44:39.60,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,请待在线外\NHold the Iine, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.68,1:44:41.96,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,请待在线外  请待在线外\NHold the Iine! Hold the Iine!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.00,1:45:29.56,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,放轻松\NTake your time.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.76,1:45:40.76,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,给我毛巾  埃迪\NLet me have that towel, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.84,1:47:58.16,BLC-50,NTP,0,0,0,,做得不错\NWell done.
